|}

Magnuson won the [[silver medal]] in the final, finishing behind [[Libby Trickett]] of [[Australia]] who had won the [[gold medal|gold]] in an [[Oceania|Oceanic]] record.<ref> [http://newsblogs.chicagotribune.com/sports_globetrotting/2008/08/magnuson-wins-s.html Magnuson wins silver in 100 butterfly]</ref> Magnuson earned her second medal, also a silver, in the 4 x 100 medley relay finishing behind team Australia.<ref>{{cite news|title=Plainsboro's Soni wins third medal, takes silver in 4 x 100 medley relay|url=http://www.nj.com/olympics/index.ssf/2008/08/plainsboros_soni_wins_third_me.html|publisher=[[The Star-Ledger]]|author=M.A. Mehta|date=August 17, 2008|accessdate=June 27, 2009}}</ref>

==2009 World Championships==
Maguson has qualified to swim in the 100 m butterfly in the 400 free relay at the [[2009 World Aquatics Championships]].

